cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel adversarial learning model for partial multi-label learning, which involves disambiguating noisy labels and mapping instances to label vectors. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on learning models and the use of deep learning techniques, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The use of image datasets in the experiments also supports the possibility of cs.CV being a likely sub-category.
